SECTION 1 — What is an Ecosystem? Definition & Scope
The fundamental unit of ecology
1.1 Definition
An ecosystem is a structural and functional unit of the biosphere consisting of a community of living
organisms (biotic components) interacting with one another and with their physical environment (abiotic
components) through the flow of energy and cycling of nutrients.
Simply put: Ecosystem = Biotic Community + Abiotic Environment + Their Interactions
