1.2 Characteristics of an Ecosystem
• It is an open system — energy enters (sunlight) and leaves (heat), matter cycles within
• It has both structure (what is present — organisms + physical environment) and function (what
happens — energy flow, nutrient cycling)
• Ecosystems are self-sustaining as long as energy input continues
• They can range in size from a small pond to the entire biosphere
• All ecosystems are interconnected — what happens in one affects others
• They have homeostatic mechanisms — ability to maintain balance through feedback
