Key Features of Producers:
• Form Trophic Level 1 (TL-1) in all food chains
• Have the maximum biomass and energy in any ecosystem
• Are primary producers of organic matter
• Fix carbon from COn into organic molecules (carbon fixation)
• Release oxygen as a by-product of photosynthesis (except purple/green sulphur bacteria)
• In terrestrial ecosystems: dominant producers are vascular plants
• In aquatic ecosystems: dominant producers are phytoplankton (microscopic algae)
• Gross Primary Production (GPP) = total photosynthesis; Net Primary Production (NPP) = GPP –
