3.3 Decomposers (Saprotrophs / Micro-consumers) — In Detail
Decomposers are microorganisms (bacteria and fungi) that break down complex organic matter from
dead plants and animals into simple inorganic substances, thereby recycling nutrients back to the
ecosystem. Without decomposers, nutrients would be locked in dead organic matter and life would cease.
